==English==

===Etymology===

Compound of ''smoke'' + ''fall''.

===Noun===

'''smokefall'''

<!-- PLEASE SEE DISCUSSION PAGE ABOUT SOURCES AND INCERTAINTIES -->
# The close of the day before [[nightfall]], when fog comes.
# The permanent twilight that could result from a nuclear war.
# A falling cloud of smoke from a large fire.
# An artificial waterfall of smoke, for shows.

